reviews.content: Very good banquet hall for gathering and celebration.. on 13th sep I went for Navratri celebration organized by Gujarati Samaj Vietnam and Indian business chamber in Vietnam.. I enjoyed very much..
Nice place,good decoration and nice big spaces with good air conditioning
Great place for weddings and company events.

This place often organizes conferences of several thousand people. Although the parking lot may seem a bit small, there are floors that are convenient for parking many cars. The price for 5 hours is 50k. …
The food is delicious. The space is suitable for company parties. The sound system is stable. The waiters are a bit slow.
The center is located right on the bank of Ben Van Don River, cool, beautiful view, eye-catching decoration, friendly staff

The wedding hall was beautiful, the food was delicious. Only the sound staff, when asked by the guests to help with the beat, had an attitude and said "I don't like it" (probably thinking that the guests were drunk and couldn't hear clearly …

This wedding venue is spacious, clean, and beautifully decorated, located on Ben Van Don Street, District 4. I've attended many events here, and generally speaking, the food is delicious, the hall has a beautiful view, and I find the cuisine here much better than many other places.

- Unprofessional service. - Cold food, just enough to taste, not delicious. The best dish is the fish with mango sauce, the taste of fish meat with mango sauce and a little spicy taste combined is not delicious (bad).
ok space, large private lobby, food is a bit cold. hot is delicious.
